1.) what is DOM
The DOM (Document Object Model) is an API for Manipulating HTML and XML documents.
The DOM Provides Functions that allow you to add, remove, and modify parts of the document effectively.


2.) What is nodes and type of nodes
The DOM represents an HTML Document as a tree of nodes, where each node is an element, or attribute, or text.
for example every html element is a node, every attribute is a node, and every text is a node. (every single line that we write in html or whatever html tags we use is a node.)


